Stephania Adediran, former Registrar of Federal Polytechnic, Ado-Ekiti, is dead. The announcement was made by Kayode Adebusuyi on behalf of the Director of Public Relations. Adediran (Badejo), served as Director of Administration at the Continuing Education Centre at the institution. Born on October 7, 1957, she was a Princess of Ijebu-Ode in Ogun and a widow of late Prof. Sunday Adegoke Adediran. The deceased joined the polytechnic as an Assistant Registrar on July 1, 1992, and was the Registrar between June 15, 2011 and February 15, 2018. “She is survived by children, grandchildren and siblings including Bishop Emmanuel Badejo of the Catholic Diocese of Oyo”, the statement read. The family will announce funeral arrangements.